). Then, the mites were recovered from the bees and re-infested in newly-capped brood cells from the LL colonies, restarting a new reproductive cycle (
Figure 1
). This procedure was repeated for three consecutive generations and, as a handling control, the removal of artificially-mite-infested cells by worker bees and mite mortality were registered at day 11 post-infestation in each generation.

